=80=9D by=C2=A0Peter DeMarzo, Erica Jiang, Arvind Krishnamurthy,=C2=A0Grego=
r Matvos, Tomasz Piskorski and Amit Seru. Their basic argument is:
=09A ton of banks have big mark-to-market losses due to interest-rate moves=
: They estimate that =E2=80=9C2,315 banks =E2=80=94=C2=A0accounting for $11=
 trillion of assets in aggregate =E2=80=94=C2=A0fall below=E2=80=9D=C2=A0ze=
ro=C2=A0equity if their assets are marked to market.=09But =E2=80=9Cthe mar=
k-to-market test =E2=80=A6 is a component of solvency, but is not determina=
nt.=C2=A0Banks have franchise value that is not reflected in the value of t=
he securities and loans they own. Thus it is likely that a large fraction o=
